    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/comment_edittext5"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:hint="Pneumonia \n \n
Pneumonia is an infection that inflames the air sacs in one or both lungs. The air sacs may fill with fluid or pus, causing cough with phlegm or pus, fever, chills,  and difficulty breathing. \n \n

Symptoms \n \n
•Cough with phlegm or pus \n
•Difficulty breathing \n
•Nausea and vomiting \n
•Rapid breathing \n
•Chest pains \n \n

Treatment \n \n
•Antibiotics (if bacterial Pneumonia) \n
•Antiviral drugs(if viral Pneumonia) \n
•Plenty of rest \n
•Fluid intake \n
•Oxygen therapy \n \n"
        android:gravity="start"
        android:inputType="none"
        android:lines="5"
        android:minLines="3"
        android:maxLines="10"
        android:textStyle="bold"
        android:scrollbars="vertical"/>


    <Button
        android:id="@+id/backpneumonia"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_below="@id/comment_edittext5"
        android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
        android:layout_marginTop="24dp"
        android:text="Back to Health Resources" />

